defs.name: raw_delete_offset
defs.docs:
Deletes all the characters from the cursor until the current position is offset position.
 
 # Examples
 ```
 t.out("Hello world!".into());
 t.raw_delete_offset(-6);
 ```
 Output: `Hello `

attributes.value: / Deletes all the characters from the cursor until the current position is offset position.

defs.name: raw_delete_from
defs.docs:
Deletes, from the start of the line, all the characters until `chars` position.
 
 # Examples
 ```
 t.out("Hello world!".into());
 t.raw_delete_from(5);
 ```
 Output: ` world!`

attributes.value: / Deletes, from the start of the line, all the characters until `chars` position.

defs.name: raw_delete_to

attributes.value: / Deletes all characters from the cursor until the x position is `x`

defs.name: choices
defs.value: fn (&self, prefix: String, strs: Vec<String>) -> String
defs.docs:
Gives the user choices between strings.
 Takes in a `prefix` to be added as a prefix on the current choice, and vector `strs` as the choices.
 The result output is a list in which options can be highlighted by using the arrow keys.
 # Examples
 ```
 let x = t.choices("-> ".into(), vec!["c1".into(), "c22".into(), "c333".into(), "c4444".into()]);
 t.outln(x);
 ```
 Output if selected was `c2`: `c2`
